1.What information can you identify for this dataset? What details are there for, or what goes into each of, the following?

Temporal/spatial coverage? -Temporal=start and end dates -Spatial= relevant data for location of data collection(lat,lon,depth) Horizontal & Vertical resolution? -grid size -depth layers Initial/boundary conditions? -starting conditions of model -boundry conditions= data for edges of model Atmospheric & riverine forcings? -atmospheric= flux conditions from atmosphere into ocean(heat,wind,precip) -riverine = salinity and nutrient flux from costal rivers Assimilated observations? -real world observations

2.Plot a horizontal slice (and vertical slice when applicable) for each of the variables within the Doppio product, for the last time within the dataset.

sea_floor_depth_below_sea_surface: ['h] sea_surface_elevation_anomaly: ['zeta] sea_water_potential_temperature: ['temp] sea_water_practical_salinity: ['salt] sea_water_x_velocity: ['u] sea_water_y_velocity: ['v]

#Horizontal slice (vert when needed)
#sea_floor_depth_below_sea_surface: ['h]
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
ds['h'].cf.plot(x="longitude", y="latitude")
plt.title("sea_floor_depth_below_sea_surface: ['h']")
plt.xlabel("Longitude")
plt.ylabel("Latitude")

#vert
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
ds['h'].isel(xi_rho=33).plot()
plt.title("Cross-Section at Longitude: xi_rho=33")
plt.xlabel("Latitude")
plt.ylabel("Depth(m)")
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()

#sea_surface_elevation_anomaly: ['zeta]
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
zeta_slice = ds['zeta'].isel(ocean_time=-1)
zeta_slice.cf.plot(x="lon_rho", y="lat_rho",cmap="coolwarm")
plt.title("Sea Surface Elevation Anomaly: ['zeta']")
plt.xlabel("Longitude")
plt.ylabel("Latitude")

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
zeta_slice.isel(xi_rho=33).plot()
plt.title("Sea Surface Elevation Anomaly:['zeta'] xi_rho=33")
plt.xlabel("Latitude")
plt.ylabel("Depth(m)")
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
